{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility/task-1","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 1","description":"","instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Slušajte audio ili dopunite sledeću rečenicu.</p>\n</section>","explanation":"<section id=\"explanation\">\n<p>Vremenski oblik <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Present Perfect Continuous</span> se koristi za opisivanje radnji koje su započele u prošlosti i koje su još uvek u toku. Fokusira se na trajanje ili kontinuitet te radnje. Struktura ovog vremena je <span class=\"highlighted-text\">have/has + been + verb(-ing)</span>. Primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">We have been developing a new app for accessibility.</span> - To znači da je razvoj počeo pre dugo i još uvek traje.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">He has been fixing bugs in the software for several hours.</span> - To znači da je počeo sa rešavanjem grešaka ranije i da je i dalje radi na tome.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>","challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"b1-english-for-developers","block":"learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility/task-1"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>Hey Sophie, BLANK you BLANK BLANK on the screen reader updates recently?</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"have","feedback":"<p>Ova reč se koristi na početku pitanja u vremenu <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Present Perfect Continuous</span> kada se pita o <span class=\"highlighted-text\">you</span>.</p>"},{"answer":"been","feedback":"<p>Ovo reči uvek prati <span class=\"highlighted-text\">have</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">has</span> kreira vreme za <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Present Perfect Continuous</span>.</p>"},{"answer":"working","feedback":"<p>Ovo je glagol u svojoj formi <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-ing</span>, što znači uložiti napor ili vreme pažljivo u završavanju vežbe ili projekta.</p>"}]},"inputType":null,"tests":[],"transcript":null,"scene":{"setup":{"background":"company2-center.png","characters":[{"character":"Tom","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"B1_4-1.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":0,"finishTimestamp":4.16},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":5.16,"dialogue":{"text":"Hey, Sophie, have you been working on the screen reader updates recently?","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Tom","position":null,"opacity":0,"startTime":5.66,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"translationPending":false}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/#learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility","dashedName":"task-1","certification":"b1-english-for-developers","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"b1-english-for-developers","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility/task-2","prevChallengePath":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility/dialogue-1-improving-screen-reader-compatibility","id":"671274ffc6d0b8654e13affe","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":19,"challengeFiles":[]}},"id":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-present-perfect-while-talking-about-accessibility/task